ts):\n\n```bash\npip install docxtpl\n```\n\n```python\nfrom docxtpl import DocxTemplate\n\n# Create template with Jinja2 syntax: {{name}}, {% for item in list %}\ncontext = {\n    \"name\": \"John Smith\",\n    \"company\": \"Acme Corp\",\n    \"items\": [\"Item 1\", \"Item 2\", \"Item 3\"],\n    \"show_section\": True\n}\n\ndoc = DocxTemplate(\"template.docx\")\ndoc.render(context)\ndoc.save(\"output.docx\")\n```\n\n## Placeholder Syntax Options\n\n| Method | Syntax | Features |\n|--------|--------|----------|\n| python-docx manual | `{{placeholder}}` | Simple replacement only |\n| docxtpl | `{{placeholder}}` | Loops, conditionals, filters |\n| native | `${placeholder}` | Custom regex patterns |\n\nThis solution handles placeholders in paragraphs, tables, headers, and footers while attempting to preserve formatting.", "solver_finish_reason": "stop"}
